reviewText:
-Extremely annoying, tedious and repetitive boss fight;
-Boring gameplay;
-Excellent graphic and soundtrack;
-Cool cutscenes;
-Good lore;
-Mediocre characters

Inferior to Darksiders, DMC, God of War.

I do not recommend this game:
* Checkpoints are too few and too far apart;
* No Checkpoints after annoying parts;

It is frustrating even for fans of challenging games;
Lords of Shadow's difficulty isn't in the challenge it presents, it is in dealing with the few checkpoints and punishing task;
You can't roll One or Two checkpoints back after a battle that left with low health and few resources;
In this case you need to go back to the start of the chapter and try to reach the same point in better conditions;
You have to replay a lot, and it gets old fast;

Sometimes after a particularly difficult battle, the player is left with little resources, low health and has two choices:

* Restart, which can make you have to replay a lot of what you have just played;
* Or push forward, hoping to find items and health and not reaching a second checkpoint that saves your game in poor conditions, making it even more punishing, forcing you to restart from the beginning of the chapter;

It's a pity;

Excellent game, with great animations, many enemies, a good plot and wonderful environments.

The good:
- Gabriel abilities and combat skills;
- the bosses, except for the Titans;
- a quite various gameplay;
- the graphics and the inspired environments.

The bad:
- the fixed camera: simply horrible and inconvenient;
- the jump system, that lacks in precision;
- the Titan battles: really boring and needlessly long.

My final rank: 9/10.

